<item>
            <title>[TIKA-310] Use TagSoup to parse HTML</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/TIKA-310</link>
                <project id="12310631" key="TIKA">Tika</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The NekoHTML library we currently use for parsing HTML has a transitive dependency on Apache Xerces. The Xerces library is pretty big (1.2MB) and is known to cause various problems when included in the classpath of an application or a container that expects some other XML parser library.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The TagSoup library (&lt;a href=&quot;http://home.ccil.org/~cowan/XML/tagsoup/&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;http://home.ccil.org/~cowan/XML/tagsoup/&lt;/a&gt;) provides an alternative HTML parsing library that works pretty much like NekoHTML but doesn&apos;t depend on Xerces. I suggest we switch from NekoHTML to TagSoup unless this change causes major regressions in HTML parsing.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
